[SN]TITLE[SN]
Biker seriously hurt in crash with van in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been seriously injured after his motorbike was involved in a crash with a van in Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It happened at about 07:35 on Friday on Croftfood Road at its junction with Bowhouse Drive.
The 46-year-old biker was taken to Queen Elizabeth University Hospital where he was being treated for chest and arm injuries.
The driver of the Vauxhall van was uninjured. Police appealed for witnesses to come forward.
